  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "μ-law G.711 audio: AU/SND container '.snd'(4B) + dataOffset(4,BE) + dataSize(4,BE,0xFFFFFFFF=streaming) + encoding(4,BE: 1=μ-law/27=A-law) + sampleRate(4,BE,=8000) + channels(4,BE,=1). Raw headerless μ-law: 8-bit samples at 8000 Hz, 64 kbps. μ-law companding maps 14-bit linear PCM to 8 bits. North American/Japanese PSTN standard. A-law is the European equivalent. Both defined in ITU-T G.711.",
    "suggestedInspections": [
