    "note": "μ-law (mu-law) and A-law are the two G.711 companding variants. μ-law is used in North American T1 circuits and Japan; A-law in European E1 circuits. μ-law has slightly better dynamic range for high-level signals. Both encode 8 bits at 8000 Hz for 64 kbps voice."
